&lt;blockquote class="callout markdown-alert callout-warning markdown-alert-warning"&gt;&lt;div class="callout-title markdown-alert-title"&gt;
 &lt;svg class="callout-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true" fill="currentColor"&gt;&lt;path d="M1 21h22L12 2 1 21zm12-3h-2v-2h2v2zm0-4h-2v-4h2v4z"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
 Warning
 &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="callout-content"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Never use double quotes inside &lt;code&gt;${{ ... }}&lt;/code&gt; as it is simply not supported.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;h2 id="tertiary"&gt;Tertiary&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GHA has a really funky tertiary: &lt;code&gt;${{ x &amp;amp;&amp;amp; 'ifTrue' || 'ifFalse' }}&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This only works if &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;ifTrue&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; isn&amp;rsquo;t the empty string. If &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;ifTrue&amp;gt; == ''&lt;/code&gt; then &lt;code&gt;''&lt;/code&gt; is considered as &lt;code&gt;false&lt;/code&gt;, which then evaluates the right hand side of the &lt;code&gt;||&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>